Introduction

Kim HyunJin is a South Korean singer-songwriter under CTDENM. She is the visual and crew commander of the girl group Loossemble. Also, she's a former member of LOONA, and its sub-unit LOONA 1/3. She was also a contestant on MIXNINE.

She released her solo single album “Hyunjin” on November 17, 2016. She debuted in LOONA on August 20, 2018, with their debut mini album “[+ +]”. However, she parted ways with BlockBerryCreative after a legal dispute.

On June 11, 2023, it was announced that she signed an exclusive contract with CTDENM. On July 29, It was also confirmed that she would debut as a member Loossemble alongside some of the other members of her group. On September 15th, 2023, she debuted as a member of Loossemble with a mini album of the same name.
